Class BackOffPolicy, long getNextBackOffMillis()

Gets the number of milliseconds to wait before retrying an HTTP request. If .STOP is returned, no retries should be made. This method should be used as follows: 
   long backoffTime = backoffPolicy.getNextBackoffMs();
   if (backoffTime == BackoffPolicy.STOP) {
     // Stop retrying.
   } else {
     // Retry after backoffTime.
   }

Upgrade warning: .getNextBackOffMillis now throws an IOException, it was not thrown prior to 1.9.

@return the number of milliseconds to wait when backing off requests, or .STOP if no more retries should be made
Class ExponentialBackOffPolicy, long getNextBackOffMillis()

Gets the number of milliseconds to wait before retrying an HTTP request. If .STOP is returned, no retries should be made.

This method calculates the next back off interval using the formula: randomized_interval = retry_interval +/- (randomization_factor * retry_interval)

Subclasses may override if a different algorithm is required.

Upgrade warning: .getNextBackOffMillis now throws an IOException, it was not thrown prior to 1.9.

@return the number of milliseconds to wait when backing off requests, or .STOP if no more retries should be made
Class GenericUrl, void appendRawPath(String)

Appends the given raw encoded path to the current .pathParts, setting field only if it is {@code null} or empty.

The last part of the .pathParts is merged with the first part of the path parts computed from the given encoded path. Thus, if the current raw encoded path is {@code "a"}, and the given encoded path is {@code "b"}, then the resulting raw encoded path is {@code "ab"}.

@param encodedPath raw encoded path or {@code null} to ignore
Class GenericUrl, List<String> getPathParts()

Sets the decoded path component by parts with each part separated by a {@code '/'} oror {@code code null} for none. @since 1.5
Class GenericUrl, void setPathParts(List<String>)

Sets the decoded path component by parts with each part separated by a {@code '/'} oror {@code code null} for none.

For example {@code "/m8/feeds/contacts/default/full"} is represented by {@code "", "m8", "feeds", "contacts", "default", "full"}.

Use .appendRawPath(String) to append to the path, which ensures that no extra slash is added.

@since 1.5

Class HttpRequest, int getContentLoggingLimit()

Returns the limit to the content size that will be logged during .execute().

If the content size is greater than this limit then it will not be logged.

Content will only be logged if .isLoggingEnabled is {@code true}.

Can be set to {@code 0} to disable content logging. This is useful for example if content has sensitive data such as authentication information.

Defaults to 16KB.

Upgrade warning: prior to version 1.9, the default was {@code 100000 (100KB)100,000} bytes, but now it is 16KB.

@since 1.7

Class HttpRequestInitializer

HTTP request initializer.

For example, this might be used to disable request timeouts: 

  public class DisableTimeout implements HttpRequestInitializer {
    public void initialize(HttpRequest request) {
      request.connectTimeoutsetConnectTimeout(0);
 = request.readTimeout =   request.setReadTimeout(0);
    }
  }

Sample usage with a request factory: 

  public static HttpRequestFactory createRequestFactory(HttpTransport transport) {
    return transport.createRequestFactory(new DisableTimeout());
  }

If you have a custom request initializer, use this more complex example: 

  public static HttpRequestFactory createRequestFactory(HttpTransport transport) {
    final DisableTimeout disableTimeout = new DisableTimeout();
    return transport.createRequestFactory(new HttpRequestInitializer() {
      public void initialize(HttpRequest request) {
        disableTimeout.initialize(request);
      }
    });
  }

Implementations should normally be thread-safe.

@since 1.4 @author Yaniv Inbar
